This paper discusses the evaluation of research organizations, which is a topic that can be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, given the focus on bibliometric and econometric evaluation methods, as well as the mention of impact and productivity, it is likely that this paper would be classified under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as well as cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the mention of measuring output and outcome suggests relevance to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
